X_i \sim \text{Poisson}(\lambda^i)
\lambda
\mathbb{P}(X_i=x_i)=e^{\lambda^i}\frac{\lambda^{i x_i}}{x_i!}
\mathcal L(\lambda;X)=\prod_i^n e^{\lambda^i}\frac{\lambda^{i x_i}}{x_i!}
\ell(\lambda;X)=C-\sum_i^n \lambda^i+(\log\lambda)\sum_{i=1}^n ix_i
 \lambda
-\sum_i^n i\lambda^{i-1}+\frac{\sum_{i=1}^n ix_i}{\lambda}=0
\sum_i^n i \lambda^i=\sum_{i=1}^n ix_i
\lambda
\sum_{i=1}^n i \lambda^i = \frac{\lambda + n\lambda^n}{1-\lambda} + \frac{\lambda-\lambda^n}{(1-\lambda)^2} - \lambda
